Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

The routes documentation does not mention allowed_methods. It only makes mention of conditions. Does this work equally well by removing all the lines that originally had "allowed_methods='...'" and only using the conditions keyword arg?

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

Ian, allowed_methods is not a part of routes, but it's our own code from here https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/stable/kilo/glance/common/wsgi.py#L649
It's used only for output messages and has no impact on system's logic. So if we write allowed_methods='My little pony' it just will print 'Allow My little pony' with 405 response :)

'conditions' limit us with set of stated in the list methods, i.e. only methods from there will be checked in RejectMethodController. In other cases (for example, method is 'INVALID') there will be 501 error, which is not right.

By removing 'conditions' we guarantee, that the server will return 405 response with correct message on all invalid methods.
